    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115C19/4</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 26, 5 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1687. Consular Agent, Bremerhaven, reports <hi rend="italic">Carib</hi>
                    apparently ran on mine 22d, 11 a. m., 10 miles west Norderney, soon sank. Three
                    of crew of thirty lost. Captain <persName>Cole</persName> and twenty-six men
                    picked up hour and half later by German scout boat <hi rend="italic">Annie
                        Busse;</hi> brought to Bremerhaven 24th, 10 p. m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
